Head: Elongate, sub-cylindrical, flattened dorsoventrally and about 1.8x longer than wide, genae very slightly narrowing towards the posterior. Vertex flat, with a slightly impressed coronal line and six irregular longitudinal rows of granules (
Fig. 10D
). Between the bases of the antennae there are two small impressions and between the eyes there is a pair of shallow swellings that are minutely and irregularly granulose. A few small granules in lower portion of genae. Eyes small, moderately projecting and slightly oval in outline; their diameter contained about 3.9x in length of genae (
Fig. 10C
). Antennae reaching to anterior margin of abdominal segment II. Scapus flattened towards the base, roundly rectangular in dorsal aspect and about 1.5x longer than wide. Pedicellus ovoid, round in cross-section and almost ¾ the length of scapus (
Fig. 10C
).

